definition: abbr. for 日本[Ri4 ben3], Japan
exterior surface/family relationship via females/to show (one's opinion)/a model/a table (listing information)/a form/a meter (measuring sth)

sentences.english: BELLISARIO: To be honest, what's changed for me is my schedule.
sentences.chinese: 老實說，變化最多的是我的日程表。

sentences.english: I use a planner or calendar that allows me to manage my time. 1.
sentences.chinese: 我用計劃表或日程表來管理時間。

sentences.english: The meeting times printed on our programs were largely theoretical.
sentences.chinese: 印在我們日程表上的會談時間基本上不算數。

sentences.english: Why does she imply that she ought to know his college schedule?
sentences.chinese: 爲什麼她要暗示她該知道他的大學日程表呢？

sentences.english: Set aside time in your schedule for dealing with information.
sentences.chinese: 從日程表上劃出處理資訊的時間。

sentences.english: Add some cross-training activities to your schedule.
sentences.chinese: 在你的日程表裏增加一些交叉訓練活動。

sentences.english: Look at my schedule make my head spin.
sentences.chinese: 看日程表就使我頭昏腦脹。

sentences.english: Put it on your schedule, and don’t miss that appointment.
sentences.chinese: 把它列入你的日程表，並且不要違反這個約定。

sentences.english: Any goal you want to accomplish: get yourself a calendar.
sentences.chinese: 對你想達成的任何目標，設一個日程表吧。

sentences.english: Before taking on any new work, look at your schedule.
sentences.chinese: 在做新的工作之前，看看你的日程表。

sentences.english: In the test plan, you can plan and track test execution schedules.
sentences.chinese: 在測試規劃中，您可以規劃並追蹤測試執行日程表。

sentences.english: Our events and happenings calendar is ' chock-a-block ' all year round.
sentences.chinese: 我們的賽事和活動日程表一年到頭都是滿滿當當的。

sentences.english: Kasia Pilewicz: Sure, do you want my schedule for everyday?
sentences.chinese: 當然可以，需要介紹我每天的日程表嗎？

sentences.english: That enables you to track coverage by schedule, as well as by environment.
sentences.chinese: 它可以讓您根據日程表或者環境來追蹤覆蓋率。

sentences.english: A shared calendar is a way of orchestrating your business or sales people.
sentences.chinese: 共享的日程表是編排業務人員和銷售人員的的手段。

sentences.english: Put it on your schedule, and don't miss that appointment.
sentences.chinese: 將它寫進你的日程表，千萬別錯過那個約定。

pinyin: dai4 ban4 shi4 xiang4 lie4 biao3

definition: never put off until tomorrow what you can do today (idiom)
pinyin: jin1 ri4 shi4 jin1 ri4 bi4
